text.section:
Before a person may ship or transport into this State any colony or used bee equipment, the person shall request an entry permit by submitting to the Department:
An inspection certificate from the state of origin;
The name, address, and state of residence of the shipper;
The person to whom and destination to which the colony or bee equipment is to be shipped;
The number of hives that contain bees;
The type and quantity of bee equipment contained in the shipment;
The date of the last official inspection of the apiary and bee equipment;
The total number of colonies in the apiary inspected;
The number of infected colonies, if any, that were found in the apiary on that last inspection; and
The number of these infected colonies that were destroyed.
